{
  "texts": [
    "This is only allowed if ℓ ≥ 𝑎 𝑐 (otherwise, the selfish miner should reveal their secret chain instead).With the MAD ledger function, if 𝑐 > 0 and the number of blocks until the last fork in the DAG (𝑎 𝑑 + 𝑐 + ℎ 𝑑 + 𝑐) is greater than 𝑁 ℓ then the honest miners' blocks that were discarded are not acceptable, making the selfish miner's blocks uncontested, yielding a reward of 𝑎 𝑑 + 𝑐.",
    "Otherwise, the honest blocks are acceptable, yielding a reward of 𝑎 𝑑ℎ 𝑑.The difficulty contribution is based on the chosen difficultyadjustment mechanism.",
    "If it is the uncontested difficulty-adjustment mechanism, a difficulty contribution of the reward plus ℓ -𝑎 𝑐 is yielded.",
    "Otherwise, 𝑎 𝑑 + ℓ is yielded.The public chain is shifted back by ℓ blocks ( ì ℎ 𝑐 ← ì ℎ 𝑐 ≪ ℓ) and the transactions that were in the discarded blocks are decremented from pool (pool ← pool -#𝑇 ì ℎ 𝑐 [: ℓ]).",
    "The selfish miner's secret chain and all other values are reset (𝑎 𝑐 ← 0, 𝑎 𝑑 ← 0, ℎ 𝑑 ← 0, p ← true).Reveal ℓ."
  ]
}